bug.short_desc: API-Viewer displays return-type 'void' for certain property getters

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1205 screenshot
example: qx.ui.list.list.getSelection()
(see attached screenshot)

This problem specifically affects properties with "check" values. In this case, the "selection" property (defined in qx.data.controller.MSelection) has the check value "qx.data.Array". In the generated doc tree, the value is "Custom check function." instead. In the 2.0.3 branch, the value is "qx.data.Array" as expected.

Fixed the test for data types as a property's 'check' value. Property getters shouldn't have a 'void' return type anyway (else they wouldn't be getters, would they?!).
